File: Supporters of former president Jacob Zuma gather outside the Pietermaritzburg High Court. AFP/Michele Spatari PIETERMARITZBURG - The supporters of former President Jacob Zuma are planning a rally this week ahead of his corruption trial on 26 May. READ: Zuma signs special plea affidavit The #HandsOffMsholozi supporters say they'll hold a prayer meeting on Tuesday at Msunduzi Freedom Park. Then on Wednesday, they'll march back to the park to show their support through song and prayer. The organisers say only 500 people will be allowed at the rally to comply with COVID-19 restrictions.